milestones.description: Collins Obuya and Alex Obanda's 143-run partnership is KENYA's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 126 between Rakep Patel and Alex Obanda
Asghar Afghan has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (16) for AFG, going past Mohammad Nabi

stories.title: Kenya coast to series win
stories.subTitle: Kenya v Afghanistan, 3rd ODI, Nairobi
stories.seoTitle: Kenya v Afghanistan: Kenya coast to series win
stories.summary: Kenya's bowlers rose to the occasion of a series-decider to hustle Afghanistan out cheaply before their batsmen chased down the runs to seal a series win in the third ODI in Nairobi

image.caption: Collins Obuya steered Kenya to victory with an unbeaten 86
